Overview of Regulated Substances 



Cheyenne Logistics Hub, L.L.C. is a 2,000-acre multi use development located southwest of Cheyenne, WY.   It was developed by Granite Peak Development and is part of the Swan Ranch project.  Four thousand acres are located at the southwest intersection of Interstate 80 (I-80) and Interstate 25 (I-25) and the remaining 3,200 acres are located across I-25 to the east.



C.L.H. operates a large private railroad switchyard that is served by the B.N.S.F. Railway (B.N.S.F.) and the Union Pacific Railroad (U.P.).   The switchyard is adjacent to the B.N.S.F. tracks on the southern end of the property and the U.P. tracks on the west side of the property.  It has a number of feeder tracks.  The High Plains Interchange (I-25 Exit 4) provides main access to the park and is located on the east side of C.L.H.   C.L.H.  may also be accessed from the College Avenue Interchange (I-25 Exit 7).  C.L.H. is platted and zoned for Heavy Industrial (H.I.), Light Industrial (L.I.) and Highway Commercial (H.C.).  



The average number of liquefied petroleum gas (L.P.G.) pressurized tank cars stored at the facility is 70, while the maximum is 120.  The average number of methanol liquid tank cars stored at the site is two, while the maximum is three.  The average and maximum diesel non-pressurized tank cars is four.  The L.P.G. DOT112J340W tank cars (33,700 gallons/ load limit 162,400 lbs.) are stored at the site by HollyFrontier Corporation.  The methanol DOT 111A100W1 non-pressurized liquid tank cars have a 30,000 gallon capacity and a 263,000 lbs. gross rail load.  The diesel tank cars are DOT111 or DOT117
